            "text": "<span class='text-muted' style='font-size:0.9em;'>(Urdu not available - English Translation)</span><br><br>Yahya related to me from Malik from Abu'z Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"The angels ask for blessings on each one of you as long as he is in the place where he has prayed and has not discharged anything. They say, 'Allah, forgive him. Allah have mercy on him.' \"\r\nMalik said, \"I do not consider that his words, 'has not discharged anything' refer to anything other than the discharges that break wudu.\"",
